376
00:34:56,898 --> 00:34:57,990
After a good night's sleep...

377
00:34:58,099 --> 00:34:59,464
i always see things better.

378
00:34:59,567 --> 00:35:00,625
Can i leave?

379
00:35:00,735 --> 00:35:02,100
Be my guest.

380
00:35:32,166 --> 00:35:33,064
Aah!

381
00:35:36,137 --> 00:35:37,468
[Coughs]

382
00:36:11,839 --> 00:36:13,534
[Door Closes]

383
00:36:47,241 --> 00:36:49,141
[Monitor Beeping]

384
00:36:57,151 --> 00:36:59,619
Hey...

385
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:02,314
are you comfortable?

386
00:37:02,423 --> 00:37:04,015
- Boss--
- Shh.

387
00:37:04,125 --> 00:37:05,114
Save your strength.

388
00:37:05,226 --> 00:37:08,855
Just tell me, who did this?

389
00:37:08,963 --> 00:37:11,659
The transporter.

390
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:14,763
The transporter's dead.

391
00:37:14,869 --> 00:37:16,769
He's not.

392
00:37:22,276 --> 00:37:23,766
Believe me.

393
00:37:26,147 --> 00:37:27,671
i believe you.

394
00:37:27,782 --> 00:37:32,014
And the police?
They were here?

395
00:37:32,119 --> 00:37:33,484
No.

396
00:37:33,587 --> 00:37:35,145
You told them nothing, right?

397
00:37:35,256 --> 00:37:37,156
Right.

398
00:37:37,258 --> 00:37:39,783
Of course...

399
00:37:39,894 --> 00:37:43,489
you couldn't talk.

400
00:37:43,597 --> 00:37:45,360
Yeah.

401
00:37:49,970 --> 00:37:51,665
Let's keep it that way.

402
00:37:51,772 --> 00:37:54,832
[Muffled Yelling]

403
00:38:01,115 --> 00:38:03,606
[Monitor Beeping Rapidly]

404
00:38:12,660 --> 00:38:14,924
[Alarm Beeping]

405
00:38:15,029 --> 00:38:17,930
[Monitor Beeping Slowly]

406
00:38:41,055 --> 00:38:42,955
[Humming]

407
00:38:50,998 --> 00:38:53,432
i picked them
from the garden outside.

408
00:38:53,534 --> 00:38:56,435
i hope you don't mind.

409
00:38:56,537 --> 00:38:59,438
i didn't know
if you like coffee...

410
00:38:59,540 --> 00:39:01,064
or tea,
so i made both.

411
00:39:01,175 --> 00:39:03,735
[Timer Rings]

412
00:39:14,155 --> 00:39:16,783
i hope you like, uh...

413
00:39:16,891 --> 00:39:19,382
" ma-de-leine.''

414
00:39:19,493 --> 00:39:21,461
Try one.

415
00:39:24,532 --> 00:39:25,965
Careful.

416
00:39:26,066 --> 00:39:27,260
it's hot.

417
00:39:30,237 --> 00:39:31,636
Good?

418
00:39:37,745 --> 00:39:39,144
Let me.

419
00:39:41,048 --> 00:39:42,777
i like it quiet in the morning.

420
00:39:42,883 --> 00:39:44,908
Yes.
Quiet in the morning.

421
00:39:45,019 --> 00:39:46,316
Me, too.
Me, too.

422
00:39:46,420 --> 00:39:50,049
i'm the same way.
i like very quiet.

423
00:39:52,226 --> 00:39:54,057
Sorry.

424
00:40:00,034 --> 00:40:01,558
Are you looking for milk?

425
00:40:02,836 --> 00:40:05,100
There's milk at the door.

426
00:40:05,206 --> 00:40:07,436
Stay, stay.
i'll go.

427
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:13,978
Hi.

428
00:40:17,351 --> 00:40:18,375
And you are?

429
00:40:18,485 --> 00:40:20,612
The new cook.

430
00:40:20,721 --> 00:40:23,155
is Monsieur Frank in?

431
00:40:23,257 --> 00:40:26,488
Ah! Monsieur Frank.

432
00:40:26,594 --> 00:40:29,654
is your invitation
for coffee still open?

433
00:40:29,763 --> 00:40:31,390
Sure, come on.
Please, sit.

434
00:40:34,034 --> 00:40:35,001
Madeleine?

435
00:40:35,102 --> 00:40:36,000
Homemade?

436
00:40:36,103 --> 00:40:37,400
Lai:
Yes.

437
00:40:37,504 --> 00:40:39,199
i'll bring some more.

438
00:40:39,306 --> 00:40:40,330
Ah.

439
00:40:40,441 --> 00:40:42,306
My mother used to make...

440
00:40:42,409 --> 00:40:43,671
fresh madeleines every morning.

441
00:40:43,777 --> 00:40:45,904
i smell them
and my whole childhood...

442
00:40:46,013 --> 00:40:48,038
comes back in one big flood...

443
00:40:48,148 --> 00:40:49,775
like Proust.

444
00:40:49,883 --> 00:40:51,510
You ever read Proust,
Monsieur Frank?

445
00:40:51,619 --> 00:40:53,086
No.

446
00:40:53,187 --> 00:40:54,347
Ah. He's fantastic.

447
00:40:54,455 --> 00:40:56,355
Memory like a steel trap.

448
00:40:56,457 --> 00:40:57,981
He would have been a great cop.

449
00:40:58,092 --> 00:40:59,059
A real detail man.

450
00:40:59,159 --> 00:41:00,683
- Milk?
- Please. Mmm.

451
00:41:02,529 --> 00:41:05,692
Thank you.
Ahh.

452
00:41:05,799 --> 00:41:08,199
Tarconi:
i used to have a memory like Proust.

453
00:41:08,302 --> 00:41:10,429
Like a filing cabinet up there.

454
00:41:10,537 --> 00:41:13,028
i would see something
and remember it like that.

455
00:41:13,140 --> 00:41:14,664
Like, uh, license plates.

456
00:41:14,775 --> 00:41:17,744
i could see a plate
and it was printed in my head.

457
00:41:17,845 --> 00:41:19,710
Now i need all
the help i can get...

458
00:41:19,813 --> 00:41:21,405
remembering whose plate...

459
00:41:21,515 --> 00:41:22,880
goes with whose car.

460
00:41:22,983 --> 00:41:26,009
Like, uh, this one.

461
00:41:28,322 --> 00:41:29,289
it's mine.

462
00:41:29,390 --> 00:41:31,654
Ah, memories.

463
00:41:31,759 --> 00:41:32,919
Frank:
So?

464
00:41:33,027 --> 00:41:34,187
Where's the rest
of the car?

465
00:41:34,295 --> 00:41:36,195
i was hoping
you could tell me.

466
00:41:36,297 --> 00:41:37,764
- it was stolen.
- Stolen?

467
00:41:37,865 --> 00:41:39,890
Yeah, i went down to Frejus
to pick up a few things.

468
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,399
When i came out
of the market, it was--

469
00:41:41,502 --> 00:41:44,403
Gone.
Did you report it?

470
00:41:44,505 --> 00:41:47,565
it's the first on my list
of things to do today.

471
00:41:47,675 --> 00:41:48,573
it's a long walk
from Frejus.

472
00:41:48,676 --> 00:41:49,643
How did you get home?

473
00:41:49,743 --> 00:41:50,903
Well--

474
00:41:51,011 --> 00:41:53,445
i brought him.

475
00:41:53,547 --> 00:41:55,913
i saw him walking
along the dark road.

476
00:41:56,016 --> 00:41:58,007
Mm, a risky thing.

477
00:41:58,118 --> 00:42:00,416
Picking up a stranger
on a dark road.

478
00:42:01,588 --> 00:42:03,419
He had a kind face.

479
00:42:06,994 --> 00:42:08,689
i didn't see
a car outside.

480
00:42:08,796 --> 00:42:09,922
it's in the garage.

481
00:42:10,030 --> 00:42:10,928
May i see it?

482
00:42:11,031 --> 00:42:12,293
Mm-hmm.

483
00:42:23,143 --> 00:42:25,043
[Birds Chirping]

484
00:42:27,348 --> 00:42:29,441
[Whistles]
Wow.

485
00:42:32,619 --> 00:42:35,281
Pretty nice car
for a cook.

486
00:42:37,558 --> 00:42:40,356
Some people have a problem
with the Germans.

487
00:42:40,461 --> 00:42:41,587
They're too aggressive.

488
00:42:41,695 --> 00:42:43,993
They take up
the best beaches in summer.

489
00:42:44,098 --> 00:42:46,123
They can't cook worth a damn.

490
00:42:49,303 --> 00:42:51,464
i say anyone
who makes such great cars...

491
00:42:51,572 --> 00:42:54,268
can't be all bad.

492
00:42:54,375 --> 00:42:56,036
i would say your intuition
worked out very well...

493
00:42:56,143 --> 00:42:57,110
for Monsieur Frank,
mademoiselle.

494
00:42:58,812 --> 00:43:01,474
Worked out for both of us.

495
00:43:05,953 --> 00:43:07,853
<i>Bon.</i>

496
00:43:07,955 --> 00:43:10,185
My intuition says
this is probably a good time...

497
00:43:10,290 --> 00:43:12,724
for me to go
file my report.

498
00:43:12,826 --> 00:43:14,293
Where's the rest
of my car?

499
00:43:14,395 --> 00:43:15,657
Oh, yes.

500
00:43:15,763 --> 00:43:17,253
i almost forgot.

501
00:43:17,364 --> 00:43:19,594
it was blown to pieces
at a rest stop.

502
00:43:20,934 --> 00:43:23,869
What's left of it
is down at the lab.

503
00:43:23,971 --> 00:43:26,439
They're trying to separate
what was left...

504
00:43:26,540 --> 00:43:28,508
of the 2 cops in the trunk...

505
00:43:28,609 --> 00:43:30,702
from the rest of it.

506
00:43:30,811 --> 00:43:33,609
But, uh, you wouldn't know
anything about that?

507
00:43:33,714 --> 00:43:35,375
No.

508
00:43:35,482 --> 00:43:36,915
Sorry to interrupt.

509
00:43:37,017 --> 00:43:39,577
Thank you for the coffee
and the memories.

510
00:43:39,686 --> 00:43:41,415
Come back any time.

511
00:43:41,522 --> 00:43:43,422
Would you mind walking me?

512
00:43:43,524 --> 00:43:45,253
Come on.

513
00:43:45,359 --> 00:43:46,826
You have always
been very quiet...

514
00:43:46,927 --> 00:43:48,758
about your business,
Monsieur Frank.

515
00:43:48,862 --> 00:43:51,695
i appreciate that.
Less work for Mother.

516
00:43:51,799 --> 00:43:53,562
But this business
at the rest stop.

517
00:43:53,667 --> 00:43:55,862
That is not very quiet.

518
00:43:55,969 --> 00:43:57,630
i don't suppose you
would like to tell me...

519
00:43:57,738 --> 00:44:00,138
something besides
a stolen car story?

520
00:44:00,240 --> 00:44:01,969
if i had one i would.

521
00:44:02,075 --> 00:44:04,873
Well, may i suggest
that when the 2 of you...

522
00:44:04,978 --> 00:44:06,741
show up in my office
after lunch...

523
00:44:06,847 --> 00:44:08,439
you do have one.

524
00:44:08,549 --> 00:44:11,040
A better one
than you currently have.

525
00:44:17,825 --> 00:44:20,055
You are the one
he wants to see...

526
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:21,058
not me!

527
00:44:21,161 --> 00:44:22,594
Quiet!

528
00:44:22,696 --> 00:44:24,755
Please, i have to think.

529
00:44:24,865 --> 00:44:26,765
You were supposed
to think last night.

530
00:44:26,867 --> 00:44:29,267
Yeah, well,
last night i had nightmares...

531
00:44:29,369 --> 00:44:32,395
about a girl who came
into my nice, quiet life...

532
00:44:32,506 --> 00:44:33,973
screwed it all up.

533
00:44:34,074 --> 00:44:35,166
Everything she touched broke...

534
00:44:35,275 --> 00:44:37,140
