00:45:46,580 --> 00:45:47,478
Uhh!

552
00:45:51,418 --> 00:45:53,477
- Aah!
- Aah!

553
00:45:53,587 --> 00:45:54,611
No, don't stay there!

554
00:45:54,721 --> 00:45:55,813
No!

555
00:45:57,758 --> 00:45:58,690
Aah!

556
00:46:04,398 --> 00:46:06,457
Aah! Aah!

557
00:46:06,567 --> 00:46:08,364
[Breathing Hard]

558
00:46:23,650 --> 00:46:24,947
Frank!

559
00:46:26,853 --> 00:46:28,286
Come on,
give me your hand!

560
00:46:32,292 --> 00:46:33,520
Aah!

561
00:46:40,634 --> 00:46:42,261
Uhh!

562
00:46:42,369 --> 00:46:44,564
Aah!

563
00:46:51,678 --> 00:46:53,976
- Aah!
- Come on!

564
00:46:56,183 --> 00:46:57,707
Come on, get in!
Get in!

565
00:46:57,818 --> 00:46:59,683
- No! No!
- Get in!

566
00:47:02,823 --> 00:47:05,587
Lai, look!
Come on, you wanna die?!

567
00:47:05,692 --> 00:47:06,920
Get in!

568
00:47:11,398 --> 00:47:13,195
[Lai Screaming]

569
00:47:26,680 --> 00:47:30,582
[Gasping]

570
00:47:30,684 --> 00:47:32,083
Calm down, OK?

571
00:47:32,185 --> 00:47:34,449
Don't worry.
You OK?

572
00:47:35,589 --> 00:47:36,851
Stay here.
i'm coming back.

573
00:47:36,957 --> 00:47:39,255
No, wait! Wait!

574
00:47:44,431 --> 00:47:45,591
Uhh!

575
00:47:49,069 --> 00:47:50,502
Aah!

576
00:47:52,506 --> 00:47:54,133
Put it on.

577
00:47:56,677 --> 00:47:57,939
- You OK?
- Mm.

578
00:47:58,045 --> 00:47:59,478
Sure?

579
00:47:59,579 --> 00:48:01,171
OK, let's go.

580
00:49:17,290 --> 00:49:19,190
[Gasps]

581
00:49:40,614 --> 00:49:42,741
Frank?

582
00:49:42,849 --> 00:49:44,578
is this your house?

583
00:49:44,684 --> 00:49:46,652
[Electric Crackling]

584
00:49:48,021 --> 00:49:49,386
Lai:
Frank?

585
00:49:49,489 --> 00:49:51,354
Uhh! Yeah, guess.

586
00:49:53,994 --> 00:49:56,258
Frank.

587
00:50:02,969 --> 00:50:05,437
i should mind
my own goddamn business.

588
00:50:07,440 --> 00:50:10,739
A simple rule.
A simple, little rule.

589
00:50:10,844 --> 00:50:12,141
There's gotta be
some dry clothes...

590
00:50:12,245 --> 00:50:15,146
in this house.

591
00:50:15,248 --> 00:50:18,945
Don't open the package.

592
00:50:19,052 --> 00:50:20,713
Nothing but trouble,
you open the goddamn package.

593
00:50:22,722 --> 00:50:23,711
Lai:
Frank.

594
00:50:28,228 --> 00:50:29,126
What are you doing?

595
00:50:29,229 --> 00:50:30,958
Making up for the trouble.

596
00:50:36,970 --> 00:50:38,460
Wait, wait.

597
00:50:38,572 --> 00:50:39,504
Why are you making--

598
00:50:39,606 --> 00:50:40,971
No more questions.

599
00:50:43,577 --> 00:50:44,601
Wait.

600
00:50:44,711 --> 00:50:46,645
i don't like it
when things get complicated.

601
00:50:46,746 --> 00:50:49,112
You like things simple.

602
00:50:49,216 --> 00:50:50,843
Very simple.

603
00:51:07,234 --> 00:51:08,929
i'm not so clear
about the house.

604
00:51:09,035 --> 00:51:11,367
Could you explain...

605
00:51:11,471 --> 00:51:13,803
uh, one more time.
After i left.

606
00:51:13,907 --> 00:51:15,875
After you left, we went
for a walk on the beach.

607
00:51:15,976 --> 00:51:17,341
- Had a swim.
- Where again?

608
00:51:17,444 --> 00:51:18,502
Past the point.

609
00:51:18,612 --> 00:51:20,273
Anyone else swimming
at that time?

610
00:51:20,380 --> 00:51:21,278
No.

611
00:51:21,381 --> 00:51:22,575
Did you see
anybody else swimming?

612
00:51:22,682 --> 00:51:24,206
No. No one.

613
00:51:24,317 --> 00:51:28,981
So, you took a walk,
had a swim...

614
00:51:29,089 --> 00:51:31,284
on a beach where no one
else was swimming...

615
00:51:31,391 --> 00:51:34,155
past the point
where you can't see...

616
00:51:34,261 --> 00:51:36,729
or be seen from the beach
on either side...

617
00:51:36,830 --> 00:51:39,526
which makes witnesses
a little hard to come by.

618
00:51:39,633 --> 00:51:42,101
That's the point
of a romantic swim.

619
00:51:42,202 --> 00:51:44,432
Who wants witnesses?

620
00:51:46,606 --> 00:51:48,005
And then?

621
00:51:48,108 --> 00:51:49,075
Then we came back
to the house...

622
00:51:49,175 --> 00:51:50,301
found it on fire.

623
00:51:50,410 --> 00:51:52,241
Just like that?
On fire?

624
00:51:52,345 --> 00:51:53,676
Yes.

625
00:51:53,780 --> 00:51:56,874
And the 5,000 rounds
of spent ammo...

626
00:51:56,983 --> 00:51:58,712
my men found
all around the house?

627
00:51:58,818 --> 00:52:00,183
Maybe they had
the wrong house.

628
00:52:00,287 --> 00:52:01,549
Monsieur Frank...

629
00:52:01,655 --> 00:52:04,453
people with
this kind of firepower...

630
00:52:04,557 --> 00:52:07,651
do not make mistakes
about who they visit.

631
00:52:08,962 --> 00:52:10,657
Who would want you this dead?

632
00:52:10,764 --> 00:52:12,493
i don't know.

633
00:52:12,599 --> 00:52:14,328
Any problems with a client?

634
00:52:14,434 --> 00:52:16,561
i don't have clients.
i'm retired.

635
00:52:16,670 --> 00:52:19,537
i live on my army pension,
you know that.

636
00:52:19,639 --> 00:52:20,571
You have all the facts
of who i am...

637
00:52:20,674 --> 00:52:22,369
and who i was.
You've had them for years.

638
00:52:22,475 --> 00:52:24,238
Any enemies
you can think of?

639
00:52:24,344 --> 00:52:25,276
People from the past?

640
00:52:25,378 --> 00:52:27,369
i left the past behind
when i moved here.

641
00:52:27,480 --> 00:52:32,247
Huh. A past like yours
you never leave behind.

642
00:52:32,352 --> 00:52:33,444
[Knock On Door]

643
00:52:33,553 --> 00:52:35,214
<i>Commissaire,</i>
<i>on vous demande en bas.</i>

644
00:52:35,322 --> 00:52:37,449
i'll just be a moment.

645
00:52:37,557 --> 00:52:38,990
Don't leave.

646
00:52:53,406 --> 00:52:54,373
What are you doing?

647
00:52:54,474 --> 00:52:56,465
Computers know everything.

648
00:52:56,576 --> 00:52:57,634
You just need a password.

649
00:52:57,744 --> 00:53:00,440
What, are you nuts?
We're in a police station.

650
00:53:00,547 --> 00:53:01,912
You're always complaining.

651
00:53:02,015 --> 00:53:04,711
Except when we make love.
Then you say nothing.

652
00:53:18,231 --> 00:53:20,324
Aha.

653
00:53:20,433 --> 00:53:22,924
Ah.

654
00:53:28,575 --> 00:53:30,304
? La la la ?

655
00:53:30,410 --> 00:53:31,741
Hello.

656
00:53:31,845 --> 00:53:33,278
See?

657
00:53:38,952 --> 00:53:40,715
[Printer Beeps]

658
00:53:52,232 --> 00:53:53,529
So, where will you be staying?

659
00:53:53,633 --> 00:53:54,861
i don't know.

660
00:53:54,968 --> 00:53:57,493
Well, my cousin
has a small hotel.

661
00:53:58,772 --> 00:54:00,899
Thanks, but we'll manage.

662
00:54:01,007 --> 00:54:03,999
Without money,
it would be hard.

663
00:54:04,110 --> 00:54:05,168
Here.
it's not much...

664
00:54:05,278 --> 00:54:07,371
but at least
you won't go hungry.

665
00:54:07,480 --> 00:54:09,778
Thank you.

666
00:54:21,761 --> 00:54:22,659
Where are you going?

667
00:54:22,762 --> 00:54:24,093
Going to see that guy.

668
00:54:24,197 --> 00:54:25,562
Good luck.

669
00:54:25,665 --> 00:54:26,859
One minute.

670
00:54:26,966 --> 00:54:28,228
You're not coming?

671
00:54:28,334 --> 00:54:29,460
No.

672
00:54:29,569 --> 00:54:31,161
But he blew up your car.

673
00:54:31,271 --> 00:54:32,568
i'll buy a new one.

674
00:54:32,672 --> 00:54:33,969
He burned your house.

675
00:54:34,074 --> 00:54:35,166
i'll rebuild it.

676
00:54:35,275 --> 00:54:36,640
He tried to kill you!

677
00:54:36,743 --> 00:54:38,404
And as far as he knows,
he succeeded.

678
00:54:38,511 --> 00:54:39,773
Look, i'm going
to give you some advice.

679
00:54:39,879 --> 00:54:40,903
i don't know
what you were into.

680
00:54:41,014 --> 00:54:42,038
i don't care
what you were into.

681
00:54:42,148 --> 00:54:43,046
But whoever wanted you dead...

682
00:54:43,149 --> 00:54:44,047
thinks you're dead.

683
00:54:44,150 --> 00:54:45,481
You have a free pass
to start over.

684
00:54:45,585 --> 00:54:48,577
Here's the advice:
Start over!

685
00:54:54,527 --> 00:54:58,156
There are 400 people dying...

686
00:54:58,264 --> 00:55:01,062
in a container on a ship.

687
00:55:03,870 --> 00:55:06,202
My father.

688
00:55:06,306 --> 00:55:08,467
My sisters.

689
00:55:08,575 --> 00:55:11,601
The ship arrives today.

690
00:55:11,711 --> 00:55:14,908
They will make
my father a slave.

691
00:55:15,014 --> 00:55:19,110
The only one who knows
the container number...

692
00:55:19,219 --> 00:55:21,619
is that guy.

693
00:55:21,721 --> 00:55:23,552
You're very good.

694
00:55:23,656 --> 00:55:25,647
What do you mean?

695
00:55:25,758 --> 00:55:27,555
The moment you saw
those pictures in my house...

696
00:55:27,660 --> 00:55:29,753
you were setting me up
to get involved in this.

697
00:55:29,863 --> 00:55:30,887
The breakfast.

698
00:55:30,997 --> 00:55:32,487
Giving the excuse
to the cop to help me.

699
00:55:32,599 --> 00:55:34,590
One lie after another.

700
00:55:34,701 --> 00:55:38,432
Not everything is a lie.

701
00:55:38,538 --> 00:55:40,768
Name one thing
that isn't?

702
00:55:43,343 --> 00:55:46,039
What happened in the house...

703
00:55:46,146 --> 00:55:47,545
between us...

704
00:55:47,647 --> 00:55:50,411
that was not a lie.

705
00:55:53,586 --> 00:55:55,178
You were a soldier.

706
00:55:55,288 --> 00:55:58,086
Your job was to save people.

707
00:55:58,191 --> 00:55:59,522
Past tense.

708
00:55:59,626 --> 00:56:00,991
What does that mean?

709
00:56:01,094 --> 00:56:02,857
it means i got tired
of seeing my best efforts...

710
00:56:02,962 --> 00:56:04,657
get turned into bullshit
by the same people...

711
00:56:04,764 --> 00:56:06,595
who paid me to do the job.

712
00:56:06,699 --> 00:56:07,859
No one cared.

713
00:56:07,967 --> 00:56:11,801
This time... i care.

714
00:56:26,853 --> 00:56:27,820
[Chuckles]

715
00:56:27,921 --> 00:56:29,354
Thank you.

716
00:56:39,666 --> 00:56:40,633
<i>Bonjour.</i>

717
00:56:40,733 --> 00:56:41,791
<i>Bonjour.</i>

718
00:56:41,901 --> 00:56:43,368
No phone calls
for half an hour?

719
00:56:44,571 --> 00:56:46,300
Hello. Surprise!

720
00:56:53,246 --> 00:56:54,474
Sit.

721
00:57:07,093 --> 00:57:08,321
Put your hands
where i can see 'em.

722
00:57:09,996 --> 00:57:11,930
So, before we get
to the heart of the matter...

723
00:57:12,031 --> 00:57:13,931
i have one question for you.

724
00:57:14,033 --> 00:57:15,330
Why'd you try to kill me?

725
00:57:15,435 --> 00:57:16,834
You lied to me.

726
00:57:16,936 --> 00:57:18,403
You opened the package.

727
00:57:18,504 --> 00:57:19,732
You broke the rules.

728
00:57:19,839 --> 00:57:20,737
Your rules.

729
00:57:20,840 --> 00:57:21,932
What did you
expect me to do...

730
00:57:22,041 --> 00:57:23,975
recommend you for another job?

731
00:57:27,547 --> 00:57:29,208
What's the ship number?

732
00:57:32,118 --> 00:57:33,949
Mr. Transporter...

733
00:57:34,053 --> 00:57:35,384
we can both agree...

734
00:57:35,488 --> 00:57:37,456
i answered your first
question politely.

735
00:57:37,557 --> 00:57:39,286
i won't answer any more...

736
00:57:39,392 --> 00:57:43,385
so i suggest
you kill me right now...

737
00:57:43,496 --> 00:57:46,158
and go screw yourself.

738
00:57:48,334 --> 00:57:50,234
i can't find anything.

739
00:57:57,176 --> 00:57:59,736
Oh, poor Frank.
What did she tell you?

740
00:57:59,846 --> 00:58:02,314
We're smuggling people
in containers?

741
00:58:02,415 --> 00:58:05,043
i tell you, " Lai'''s
the perfect name for her.

742
00:58:05,151 --> 00:58:06,550
Secretary, On intercom:
Mr. Kwai's on the way up.

743
00:58:06,653 --> 00:58:07,551
Your father's here.

744
00:58:07,654 --> 00:58:09,679
He'll really get
a kick out of this.

745
00:58:09,789 --> 00:58:11,381
i thought your father
was in a container.

746
00:58:11,491 --> 00:58:13,288
Yes! i--i mean, no.

747
00:58:13,393 --> 00:58:15,884
There are 400 people
in that container.

748
00:58:16,996 --> 00:58:18,657
Stay where you are!

749
00:58:18,765 --> 00:58:21,256
She's a real heartbreaker,
isn't she, Frank?

750
00:58:23,536 --> 00:58:25,561
1 0 seconds, 2 choices.

751
00:58:25,672 --> 00:58:28,072
The information on the paper
or your brains on the desk!

752
00:58:28,174 --> 00:58:29,334
Now tell me i'm lying!

753
00:58:29,442 --> 00:58:30,909
- 9...8...
- Frank: Lai.

754
00:58:31,010 --> 00:58:32,602
Lai, give me
the gun.

755
00:58:32,712 --> 00:58:33,838
i don't know
what you're talking about.

756
00:58:33,946 --> 00:58:35,675
...6...5...

757
00:58:35,782 --> 00:58:37,477
4...3...

758
00:58:37,583 --> 00:58:38,481
2...

759
00:58:38,584 --> 00:58:39,846
...one.

760
00:58:39,952 --> 00:58:41,078
Shoot.

761
00:58:42,188 --> 00:58:44,281
[Laughs]

762
00:58:45,425 --> 00:58:46,449
Lai!

763
00:58:46,559 --> 00:58:48,459
[Speaking Chinese]

764
00:58:54,534 --> 00:58:57,401
Would i kill
my own daughter?

765
00:58:57,503 --> 00:59:00,404
Lai.

766
00:59:00,506 --> 00:59:03,100
Come on now.

767
00:59:03,209 --> 00:59:04,403
Put it down.

768
00:59:07,847 --> 00:59:09,314
We'll talk.

769
00:59:09,415 --> 00:59:13,146
She thinks we're smuggling
people in containers.

770
00:59:14,787 --> 00:59:16,049
i don't know where
you get these ideas!

771
00:59:16,155 --> 00:59:17,144
Stay away!

772
00:59:21,761 --> 00:59:24,491
Would you kill
your own father?

773
00:59:24,597 --> 00:59:26,155
Please...

774
00:59:26,265 --> 00:59:27,823
i am begging you.

775
00:59:27,934 --> 00:59:29,629
Stop what you are doing.

776
00:59:29,736 --> 00:59:31,465
i do what i do.

777
00:59:31,571 --> 00:59:32,833
i am who i am.

778
00:59:32,939 --> 00:59:34,065
i'll never change.

779
00:59:34,173 --> 00:59:36,539
So if you're
going to kill me...

780
00:59:36,642 --> 00:59:37,700
kill me.

781
00:59:37,810 --> 00:59:39,801
But if you don't...

782
00:59:39,912 --> 00:59:41,174
get this gun
out of my face!

783
00:59:45,017 --> 00:59:46,075
[Snaps]
Give me.

784
00:59:46,185 --> 00:59:47,152
No!

785
00:59:47,253 --> 00:59:48,151
[Speaks Chinese]

786
00:59:48,254 --> 00:59:49,653
i know he's innocent.

787
00:59:49,756 --> 00:59:51,553
Oh, you have
such a good heart.

788
00:59:51,657 --> 00:59:54,751
Always interested in
saving innocent people.

789
00:59:54,861 --> 00:59:56,488
Well, here's
your big chance.

790
00:59:56,596 --> 00:59:57,756
Drop your gun...

791
00:59:57,864 --> 01:00:00,355
and you will save one.

792
01:00:02,802 --> 01:00:03,894
[Chuckles Smugly]

793
01:00:05,838 --> 01:00:07,430
- Kill him!
- No!

794
01:00:07,540 --> 01:00:10,373
[Telephone Rings]

795
01:00:10,476 --> 01:00:11,909
The police are
on their way up.

796
01:00:12,011 --> 01:00:13,478
- What now?
- Take her.

797
01:00:15,882 --> 01:00:17,110
Send in Leo.

798
01:00:17,216 --> 01:00:18,740
i need him to wrap
something up.

799
01:00:35,067 --> 01:00:36,091
Just for the record...

800
01:00:36,202 --> 01:00:38,397
there aren't 400 people
in that container.

801
01:00:38,504 --> 01:00:42,440
Only 395 made it here alive.

802
01:00:42,542 --> 01:00:44,203
Frank!

803
01:00:47,680 --> 01:00:49,773
inspector.
Am i glad you're here.

804
01:00:50,983 --> 01:00:51,150
What is this?

805
01:00:51,150 --> 01:00:52,048
What is this?

806
01:00:52,151 --> 01:00:54,085
This man used
my partner's daughter here...

807
01:00:54,187 --> 01:00:55,552
to try and blackmail us.

808
01:00:55,655 --> 01:00:58,215
Luckily, my security
got the drop on him.

809
01:00:59,325 --> 01:01:01,054
i wanna press charges--
kidnapping...

810
01:01:01,160 --> 01:01:02,457
extortion, assault.

811
01:01:02,562 --> 01:01:03,824
i know this man.

812
01:01:03,930 --> 01:01:05,727
Well, i suppose
in your business...

813
01:01:05,832 --> 01:01:07,857
you have to know all types.

814
01:01:10,002 --> 01:01:11,902
Now, should i call my lawyer?

815
01:01:12,004 --> 01:01:13,596
We'll handle it.

816
01:01:18,978 --> 01:01:20,411
i'll expect all of you...

817
01:01:20,513 --> 01:01:22,242
down at my office
to give your statements.

818
01:01:22,348 --> 01:01:24,145
As soon as i contact
my lawyer...

819
01:01:24,250 --> 01:01:26,241
we'll be more
than happy to oblige.

820
01:01:34,227 --> 01:01:36,320
Ohh. Mmm...

821
01:01:46,072 --> 01:01:47,437
The doctor said
you will have a headache...

822
01:01:47,540 --> 01:01:49,303
for a few days
and then everything...

823
01:01:49,408 --> 01:01:50,670
will go back to normal.

824
01:01:50,776 --> 01:01:51,708
Where are they?

825
01:01:51,811 --> 01:01:54,336
Ah, i think you should
